COPY public.garden_plants (id, user_id, scientific_name, common_name, hindi_name, description, uses, benefits, native_region, growing_conditions, is_poisonous, toxicity_details, image_url, notes, created_at) FROM stdin;
bf5e7617-3817-4166-b601-23b8c0c40ec4	1adb2fbd-6c2b-4b69-92f4-3e91c1354d4b	Ocimum tenuiflorum	Tulsi, Holy Basil	तुलसी (Tulsi)	Tulsi, also known as Holy Basil, is an aromatic perennial plant in the family Lamiaceae. It is native to the Indian subcontinent and widely cultivated throughout Southeast Asia. It is revered in Hinduism and often planted near Hindu temples. The plant has oval-shaped leaves with slightly serrated edges and emits a strong, characteristic aroma.	- Used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine\n- Brewed as a herbal tea\n- Added to food for flavor and potential health benefits\n- Used in religious ceremonies\n- Insect repellent	- Boosts immunity\n- Reduces stress and anxiety\n- Aids digestion\n- Provides relief from cough and cold\n- Purifies the blood	Indian Subcontinent	Tulsi thrives in warm, sunny conditions with well-drained soil. It prefers a slightly acidic to neutral pH. Water regularly, but avoid overwatering. Protect from frost.	f	Toxicity details not specified	https://oncincpadumklocxmatf.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/plant_images/plant_1750358091760.jpeg	\N	2025-06-19 18:34:56.127297+00
6c4ec241-9996-4b44-8b86-d3c254ff2211	1adb2fbd-6c2b-4b69-92f4-3e91c1354d4b	Cordyline fruticosa	Cordyline	N/A	Cordyline is a genus of about 15 species of monocotyledonous flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae, subfamily Lomandroideae. They are native to the western Pacific Ocean region, from New Zealand, eastern Australia, southeastern Asia and Polynesia, with one species found in southeastern South America.	- Ornamental plant\n- Landscaping\n- Indoor decoration	- Air purification\n- Low maintenance\n- Adds tropical flair to indoor spaces	Western Pacific Ocean region	Well-draining soil, bright indirect light, moderate watering, warm temperatures, high humidity.	t	Toxic to cats and dogs; can cause vomiting, depression, and loss of appetite if ingested.	https://oncincpadumklocxmatf.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/plant_images/plant_1750385055833.jpeg	\N	2025-06-20 02:04:17.795319+00
799634e0-ec1f-4051-988d-175a61ff8f51	704351e0-82fa-4df7-82e1-46928c736cf7	Ocimum tenuiflorum	Tulsi, Holy Basil	तुलसी (Tulsi)	Tulsi, also known as Holy Basil, is an aromatic perennial plant in the Lamiaceae family. It is characterized by its oval-shaped green or purple leaves, square stems, and small, fragrant flowers arranged in spikes. It is considered a sacred plant in Hinduism and is often grown in homes and temples.	- Used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine\n- Leaves can be chewed raw or brewed into tea\n- Used in religious ceremonies\n- Added to food for its flavor and health benefits\n- Used in skincare products	- Helps to reduce stress and anxiety\n- Boosts immunity\n- Has anti-inflammatory properties\n- Aids in digestion\n- Can help lower blood sugar levels	Indian subcontinent	Tulsi prefers warm, sunny locations with well-drained soil. It requires regular watering and protection from frost. It can be grown in pots or directly in the ground.	f	Toxicity details not specified	https://oncincpadumklocxmatf.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/plant_images/plant_1750389511383.jpeg	\N	2025-06-20 03:18:35.834577+00
ae262f00-0cd2-4cd4-94de-18970251cfd9	a1ec9284-cc1a-4826-bccb-c3de4193958d	Lilium	Lily	N/A	Lilies are bulbous herbaceous perennials, forming underground scaly bulbs. They produce striking flowers that are large, often fragrant, and come in a wide range of colors including whites, yellows, oranges, pinks, reds, and purples. They are popular ornamental plants.	- Ornamental plant in gardens and bouquets\n- Used in traditional medicine in some cultures	- Adds beauty and fragrance to gardens\n- Some species have medicinal properties (though use with caution and expert advice)	Mostly temperate Northern Hemisphere	Well-drained soil, full sun to partial shade, regular watering during growing season	t	Highly toxic to cats; can cause kidney failure. Some varieties are mildly toxic to humans and dogs, causing gastrointestinal upset.	https://oncincpadumklocxmatf.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/plant_images/plant_1757668005543.jpeg	\N	2025-09-12 09:06:47.889664+00
\.


